Architect Michael Arad's "Reflecting Absence" design, chosen from over 5,000 entries, will feature two reflecting pools symbolizing the void left by the 9/11 attacks.
Former US presidents and prominent figures have pledged support for the memorial project.
The memorial will honor the victims and preserve their stories for future generations.
The memorial will include a public space for visitors to locate their loved ones' names.
The foundation aims to raise $500 million for the memorial and cultural facilities.
The memorial is set to be completed by 2009, providing a place for remembrance and reflection on the tragic events of September 11th
